<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-01-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="746" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d746">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">McCormick</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-04"><hi rend="italic">January 4,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay instructs Mr. McCormick to ascertain the status of the <hi rend="italic">Calchas</hi>, whether the appeal by the Russian
                            procurer was against the entire decision of the Vladivostok prize court
                            covering vessel and cargo; and if appeal did not extend to the cargo to
                            ascertain what disposition was made of the merchandise declared to be
                            noncontraband.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>